The paper discusses a linear programming model for the Traveling Salesman Problem, which is a well-known problem in combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which can be related to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.RO (Robotics). The modeling approach can be considered as a form of artificial intelligence, which can be linked to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves mathematical programming, which can be related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
